name: Target
directions: As soon as you come in, before guest services, turn left and it's first door on you left
comment: Open Mon-Sat 8am-10pm; Sun 8am-9pm

name: UNC Campus - Brooks Bldg
directions: Across Columbia St. from the Carolina Inn.Room FB109 on first floor, SW corner.One flight up from the front entrance.Fully accessible.  Elevator is on the East corridor.
comment: This is a lockable one-holer, with gender marker sign indicating male and female.Building is open to the public from 7:30AM to 5:30PM M-F.  Not sure about weekends.

name: Kohls Department store
directions: back of the store by the service counter

name: Basement of Dreese Laboratories
directions: In the basement. Also accessible from the north stairs to the basement in Baker Systems if you feel like a leisurely stroll.

name: Academy of Art University
directions: On the entrance level of the building, walk straight to the back and it's on the right. It's a gender neutral multi-stall bathroom.
comment: Only available for Academy students with ID

name: Academy of Art University
directions: Two neutral single-stall bathrooms each on the 1st and 2nd floors. Way in the back, near the back staircase.
comment: Only available for Academy students with ID

name: Pottery Barn @ The Summit Mall
directions: In the back of the store on the left side

name: Publix
directions: Go upstairs to the store.Go to aisle #9.Restrooms are all the way in the back.
comment: Opens at 7am, closes at 10pm.

name: Java Jolt
directions: IN Back

name: Foundry Building
directions: There are two sets of bathrooms.  The downstairs ones (Lower Level) next to the Cafe and CDIA are unlocked and completely free.  There are also Key Entry bathrooms on the Lobby Level.  You get the key from the guard.  After 5 the guard is gone and leaves the keys on the desk

name: Northtown Mall
directions: Upper floor, by the food court
comment: Non-gendered stalls that lock, called \"family bathrooms\". Have a cute mini toilet for young 'uns

name: atlas cafe
comment: a guy once died in this bathroom. ask the barista about it

name: verb cafe
comment: not very clean though

name: Autopia Biofuels
directions: From 101 exit 3rd ave west. Left on Delaware. Right on 9th. Left on S.Railroad
comment: Clean, Air Conditioned, Hypo Allergenic TP!

name: Gigibar
comment: - 6:30a-6p daily (7a open on Sunday)- friendly staff

name: Cambridge City Hall Annex
directions: walk in main doorgo up main stairway which is straight aheadbathrooms are in a short corridor on the left
comment: bathrooms are single stall and \"gender unspecified\"open weekdays Hours:8:30 - 8:00    Monday8:30 - 5:00    T/W/Th8:30 - 12:00  Friday

name: Marshall Square Fitness Center
street: Corner of University Ave & Marshall St
directions: 1st floor of the Marshall Square Mall right next to Syracuse University.
comment: This restroom is IN the fitness center.  I think you need an SU ID to enter.

name: McCoy Stadium /Pawtucket Red Sox
directions: There are family bathrooms that are single, locking rooms. These are found between the men's/women's bathrooms. There is atleast 2 of them, but there is probably more like 3 or 4. The sign says family bathroom and a smaller sign is designated with a male/female/wheelchair accessible bathroom sign.
comment: This is especially great because the men's bathhrooms has 20,000 urinals and 3 stalls.

name: The Grape
directions: Straight back from the main entrance, just past the bar.  One genderfree and one women's (don't ask WHY it's that way) bathroom, both single-use and locking.

name: brookfield square mall
comment: This is a family bathroom open to either gender, but unfortuantly it is under construction and closed at the moment.  It is located in the food court area

name: Subway Restaurant
directions: In back, there's a single genderfree bathroom.
comment: Open 7:00am to 10:00 pm.  Fairly cheap food, so if anyone challenges you using the bathroom, you can get something for ~$3 to justify using it.

name: Kendall Hall, Bio Sci Library
directions: In the lobby on the first floor.  Right in front of you.
comment: Open any time the building is open

name: Wired Monk
directions: one on the main floor, one in the basement

name: Waffle House
directions: Go in and to the left. Bathrooms are down a small hallway.
comment: They're often skanky, but waffle Houses tend to have single-person bathrooms. Remember that next time you take a roadtrip.

name: siri Thai
directions: One on the upper floor (enter from Finley st or go up the stairs) one on the lower floor (enter from Prince Ave). Both genderfree.

name: Water Business Office #1
directions: go in the front door and head halfway down the hallway to your left, as though you're heading to the customer service area in the back.
comment: Open 9-5, I think.

name: downtown business building
directions: The 3rd floor restroom is gender-free - tucked down the hallway just left of the elevators.
comment: The building locks at 6 PM

name: Mariposia Food CoOp
directions: right side of the store in the back, near the teas and herbs.
comment: Hours:Monday - Thursday: noon - 9 pmFriday, Saturday and Sunday: 11 am - 6 pm(Off hours shopping for members in good standing 6+ mos)

name: Whale's Rib
directions: There are two unisex bathrooms as you come in the main entrance(left side of building from an outside dining patio)
comment: If you happen to find yourself in this part of Maine, they are very laid-back, and you might be able to just come in to use their bathroom.

name: Quiznos
directions: Past the counter, in the back.

name: Mama's Boy
directions: Go in and turn left. bathrooms are down a small hallway.
comment: Open for Breakfast and Lunch 7 days a weekOpen for Supper Thursday through SundayOpen for Brunch Saturday and Sunday

name: Cali n' Tito's
directions: Go around back, outside the building. 2 locking bathrooms are on the rear of the building.
comment: The food is awesome. And as of this writing, you don't need a key to use tha bathroom, they're left unlocked during business hours.

name: Mod
directions: Walk in either set of doors and head for the back left corner. It is one CLEAN bathroom.

name: Mayfair mall
directions: 2nd floor in food courtAlso 1st floor too
comment: there are two single stall gender neutral (family) bathrooms in the food court on the second floor.  Also there is one family bathroom on the 1st floor down a hallway leading to the reg. bathrooms and mall suites.

name: Espresso Royale
directions: Go in to the rear. There are 2 bathrooms in an alcove slightly to the right of the bar.
comment: Coffee's pretty good too. Can't remember if the side door is level with the sidewalk; the front door is up a step.

name: 283 Bar
directions: Go in to the back of the bar. Restroom is large and comfortable, in the right-rear of the room.
comment: Sometimes there's a bouncer at the front door, so you might need to be 21 to get in. Front door is up 3 or 4 stairs.

name: Taco Stand
directions: When facing the front door outside the building, look to your left, There is a outdoor covered hallway down the side of the building, with men's and women's single-occupancy bathrooms.
comment: May be less than wheelchair accessible when employees stack shit in the hallway for temporary storage. Open during the restaurant's business hours.

name: Waffle House
street: just east of I-35 on S 19th St
comment: men's and women's single locking bathrooms, handicap access, I've never had issues with anyone at this Waffle House with service

name: Gourmet Burgers
comment: Family owned restaurant.

name: Main Squeeze
directions: At the back, to the right of the counter.
comment: The Main Squeeze is a pretty amazing restaurant, so buy some food if you can--but I don't think they'd throw a desperate genderqueer out on the street if you're broke and need to pee.

name: Tyler Galleria Food Court
directions: Right between the Mexican grill and the Japanese place, across from the gendered bathrooms
comment: It's a \"family\" bathroom. whatever, just walk in, lock it, and do whatever yr doing

name: Torrey Pines State Beach
street: 12500 North Torrey Pines Road, San Diego CA 92037
comment: Multiple sexfree locking single stalls. Sinks outside. Also one of the nicest beaches in San Diego!

name: Oryana Food Cooperative
directions: Bathrooms are located behind the kitchen/cafeteria. If you go in the Lake Street door, the bathrooms are right there on the right. Map here http://www.oryana.coop/map.html
comment: Queer-friendly store. Two gender-neutral single-use very clean accessible bathrooms. Each has 1 toilet, 1 waterless urinal and 1 sink. ETA- There are also two single use, gender neutral bathrooms on the other side of the store.

name: Southern Oregon University Library Coffee Shop
directions: Coffee shop is just to the left of the main library entrance.
comment: Hours vary. There is also a little gender free bathroom in the student cafeteria in the Union.

name: Carousel Antique Mall
directions: At the front of the store, next to the coffee machine and drinks cooler, across from the cash register.

name: Chipotle
directions: very visible, adjacent to the dining room.
comment: While I'm not confident that the business, itself, is particularly trans-friendly, I've eaten there and used both restrooms without any hostile interactions (or even funny looks), as have several pre-transition transwomen and transmen, and gender non-conforming gay folks I'm friends with.

name: Zoomdweebie's Tea Bar
directions: Visible from the front door--the bathrooms are located down the building's only hallway.
comment: It's not imperative that you buy anything; plenty of people wander in and out without doing so.  But it's a small business, and it's queer friendly, so please do!I've used both male and female restrooms without question or interference; a sizeable number of customers are gay/trans, and the owner and manager are both pretty open and supportive.

name: Super Target
directions: front of the store in the middle.
comment: AMAZING family restroom/nursing room. Also gender-neutral fitting rooms

name: Milwaukee Theatre
directions: Seven locking, single-stall 'family' restrooms - three on the first floor and two each on the mezzanine & balcony levels, adjacent to the men's and women's restrooms.
comment: Available only to patrons/attendees at events.

name: Home Hardware
directions: Back right hand corner of the store, one gender neutral washroom, one single locking men's room also.
comment: Not really a trans/pride friendly place, but if you're looking for safe & private it's ok.

name: Larry's Giant Subs
directions: In the back past the soda machine

name: Ramsey Student Center
directions: You enter on the 2nd floor. Go to the right-hand side of the building and go down to the first floor, by elevator or stairs. Go down the long hallway past the rock climbing wall, follow the signs or ask directions to the 'family changing rooms'

name: Daily Grocery Co-op
directions: Bathroom is in the back room, accessible from the left-rear corner of the store.
comment: Go in and ask the clerk if you can use the restroom. They always say yes, but it's rude to walk in without saying anything--they might think you were trying to steal from the storage room. Open till 10PM every day.

name: The Grit
directions: 2 single-person bathrooms at the back of the restaurant, in the main room.

name: The Grill
directions: Go in to the back, bathrooms are in the back left corner
comment: Open 24-7, except some major holidays. On weekend nights the staff may make you buy something or bribe the cashier with a tip ($1 should do) to use the bathroom if you're not eating there. Restrooms are hypothetically ADA compliant, but the hallway leading to them is a tight fit and the bathrooms are small, so it might be easier to go elsewhere downtown

name: East Side Kroger
directions: Go into the store and make a hard right. Bathrooms are in the front-right corner just past the little Starbucks kiosk.
comment: Store is open 24-7, except major holidays.

name: Latty's Giant Subs
directions: go all the way to the back. the bathroom will be on your left, with 2 signs on the same door (I'm guessing the franchise expected a 2-bathroom set-up)
comment: Open for lunch & dinner 7 days a week.

name: Glenn Restaurant
directions: Small family restaurant approx. 15 miles south of Saugatuck, MI right off Blue Star Highway (A2).  Walk towards the back door, past the coffee station.
comment: It has two one-person, gender-free bathrooms with locks.  You shouldn't have to wait to enter a one-person bathroom just because the sign on the door is not your gender (dumb).  The door locks, for Pete's sake!  LOL

name: Florida State University
directions: One genderfree 'handicap' single-person restroom on each floor
comment: Hours are 8-5, unless a student has after-hours card-access

name: All Saints Cafe
directions: 1st floor
comment: Open 24 hours, local independent cafe hang-out

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In the back by the produce.
comment: Open 9am-9pm.

name: Squalicum Medical Office Plaza
directions: West of St Joseph's Hospital. Just outside suite 180
comment: Single occupancy locking gendered accessible bathrooms--low volume.

name: Local Color
directions: On the main road in Pike Place market, cross street Pine.
comment: Coffee shop with art for sale.www.localcolorseattle.comFree wifi.

name: Kohl's
directions: Rear left of building at customer service.

name: University of Oregon
directions: First floor, Condon Hall.

name: University of Oregon
directions: First Floor, Deady Hall.  Across the hall from room 106.
comment: Hours are only during the hours of building.

name: Cinemark Theatres
directions: The movie theatre in the mall.
comment: It's a family restroom.  You must buy a ticket for a movie to access it as it is behind the ticket counter.

name: The Little India
directions: In the back of this small Indian restaurant.
comment: Nice, clean unisex restroom. Food is not fabulous, but good enough if you are in the mood for Indian and are in the neighborhood.

name: Casa Que Pasa
directions: First right after you go in the door. There are two accessible, gendered, single-use locking bathrooms (one men's, one women's) AND one gender-free bathroom, but that one is not wheelchair accessible.

name: Nicks Pizza
directions: in back, ask and they'll give you directions
comment: yummy veggie pizza place. they have vegan slices!!

name: Nabolom Bakery
directions: in the way back behind the counter and to the left.
comment: worker co-op bakery, vegan treats.

name: Nomad Cafe
directions: behind the coffee bar
comment: a great little, chill cafe!

name: Lanesplitter Pizza
directions: In the back
comment: A delicious pizza pub. vegan options too!

name: Northpark Center
directions: Gendered restrooms on first floor across from mall offices. Gendered and \"family\" restrooms on second floor near food court. Gendered restrooms in the anchor department stores.
comment: An upscale mall, lots of foot traffic.

name: Transmetropolitan
directions: On the ground floor, there are 2 gendered single stall bathrooms at the back on your left, which are wheelchair accessible. The bar on the second floor also has 2 gendered single person bathrooms, which are only accessible by a flight of stairs.
comment: Anytime they\\'re open, you can pretty much walk in and no one will notice. The only exception might be during major street festivals, hen they\\'d rather keep bathrooms customers only.

name: Pomerene Hall
directions: Same building as Mirror Lake Cafe and the Office of Disabilities. Ground floor, open the door with the restroom sign on it walk down the hall, and there are two gendered restrooms, I know the male one locks equipped with a urinal and toilet.
comment: not sure the hours

name: Slacks Resturant and Bar
directions: Head straight in and go towards the back. Go down the flight of stairs and bathrooms are at the bottom of the stairs.
comment: There is a mens and women's room, but both sexes use them interchangably, and this is a queer establishment. Open from 4:30pm - 2AM and closed on Mondays.

name: The Slice
directions: First floor, pizza joint. Only one bathroom. Has a toilet and a urinal. One stall, locking.

name: Javawerks
directions: take a left when you walk in the door and go all the way back; bathrooms are on the right.
comment: normally 5 to 11, during finals week at the university of southern mississippi they stay open 24 hours.

name: University of Colorado
directions: Every floor

name: University of Colorado
directions: Every floor

name: All Souls Unitarian Universalist Church
directions: church has several gender-neutral bathrooms in various locations throughout the church, in addition to the two traditional-gendered bathrooms. some of them are often locked, but the one directly in front of the southeast entrance (on the left side of the building if coming in from the parking lot) is the easiest and most accessible. it has a stall with a door that locks, urinal and sink are outside the stall.

name: The Mix
directions: through the 2nd brown curtain on the left
comment: 7am - 2pm

name: LifeJourney Church
directions: The genderfree bathroom is a little bit hidden -- in the front of the church there are two traditional-gendered bathrooms, but if you walk past those, turn left (away from the social hall/sanctuary), walk down the hall past the offices/classrooms, and turn right at the last hallway before the exit, you will find a single-stall, gender-neutral bathroom at the end of that hall on your right.
comment: LifeJourney Church is a GLBTQ-affirming church. INTRAA and IndyBoyz/IndyGirlz hold meetings there.

name: Flaco's Cuban Bakery
directions: Walk in the door and head past the ordering counter down to the hallway. The bathroom is right there, before the bar room.
comment: the sign on the bathroom door, at one time at least, said \"women, men, transgender, whoever!\" the staff is nice and most of the customers are punk, so there should be no problems here.

name: Bond Hall, WWU
directions: Bond is the building on the south side of Red Square on WWU's campus. The bathrooms are on the mezzanine floors, on the east side of the building.

name: Louise Anderson Hall, Eastern Washington University
CVS Drugstore
directions: In the strip mall with Wild Oats, a Boat place, and some nice little stores.
comment: The bathroom here is always sooo bad you can not believe it. The stench of stale human urine is detectable when approaching this  festering hellhole. I worked in the Sewage and Wastewater industry for years, yet this bathroom was still nearly too much for me.Think they just forgot to clean this week.. no way! It's been like this since I first had to use it in 2006They must have a separate restroom for the employees because it is an F-ing horror-show in there.

name: The Hint Cafe
directions: in the back
comment: Queer owned cafe

name: Jiffy Lube
directions: In waiting room
comment: Phone: 630-893-8844Store Hours:Sun: 9:00 AM-4:00 PMMon-Fri: 8:00 AM-7:00 PMSat: 8:00 AM-5:00 PM

name: Upper Dublin Public Library
directions: In the library straight back from the front door. The center door is the gender free bathroom.

name: AIDS Vancouver Island
directions: Enter through the front door, walk along the hallway right in front of you then turn right. Walk into the supply room turn left and it's right there.

name: Sonic Drive-In
directions: Exterior entrance on the side of the building
